                <h1>What Disqualifies You from Being a Caregiver?</h1>
                <p>Disqualifications for becoming a caregiver include a history of abuse, criminal convictions, substance abuse issues, or failure to pass background checks. Inadequate training, lack of necessary certifications, and medical disqualifications also play a role. These factors ensure safety and quality care for those in need.</p>
